casebody.data:
State
v.
Gilbert 2018-0461 Supreme Court of Ohio. June 6, 2018

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

On review of an order certifying a conflict. The court determines that a conflict exists. Sua sponte, cause held for the decision in 2017-1703, State v. Dangler, and briefing schedule stayed.

Kennedy, French, and DeWine, JJ., dissent in part and would determine that a conflict exists and order the parties to proceed pursuant to S.Ct.Prac.R. 8.03.
